.TH "atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_pulse" 9 "atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_pulse" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_pulse \- set the SMC CS conf xx_PULSE parameter to a specific value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_pulse
.BI "(struct atmel_smc_cs_conf *conf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int shift "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ncycles "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "conf" 12
SMC CS conf descriptor
.IP "shift" 12
the position of the xx_PULSE field in the PULSE register
.IP "ncycles" 12
value (expressed in MCK clk cycles) to assign to this xx_PULSE
parameter
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function encodes the \fIncycles\fP value as described in the datasheet
(section "SMC Pulse Register"), and then stores the result in the
\fIconf->setup\fP field at \fIshift\fP position.

Returns -EINVAL if \fIshift\fP is invalid, -ERANGE if \fIncycles\fP does not fit in
the field, and 0 otherwise.
